  OBJECTIVES OF THE DATABASE SYSTEM
1.	To store and manage client information efficiently
The system will maintain accurate records of clients including their identification 
details, contact information, and banking accounts.
2.	To record and track financial transactions
The database will store transaction details such as the transaction ID, transaction
 amount, type, and date to ensure proper tracking of financial activities.
3.	To manage digital wallets and bank accounts
The system will maintain wallet balances and account information to support mobile
 banking services.
4.  To manage loan records for clients
Loan information such as loan ID, loan amount, payment dates, and loan status will 
be stored and managed in the database.
5.  To ensure secure user authentication
The system will store login credentials and authentication details to verify users
 before allowing access to the mobile banking system.


Main Operations Supported by the Database
The system will support several important operations including:
o	Storing data such as client information, accounts, wallets, and devices
o	Retrieving data such as account balances and transaction history
o	Updating records when transactions occur or when user information changes
o	Managing transactions including transfers, deposits, and payments
o	Authenticating users during login to ensure secure access to the system
